# Security Review: `app.js`

The file is a 22-line Express stub with two endpoints (`/health`, `/users`) returning hardcoded data. There is no database, authentication, user input handling, or dynamic logic — so most OWASP Top 10 categories (injection, SSRF, deserialization, etc.) have no surface to attack here. That said, several hardening issues and latent concerns are worth addressing before this grows.

## Findings

### 1. No authentication / authorization (OWASP A01: Broken Access Control)
`/users` exposes PII (names + email addresses) with no auth. Even in a demo, establish the pattern early.

